1201
01:26:49,512 --> 01:26:52,432
I think I deserve
a little better than that.

1202
01:26:55,269 --> 01:26:58,940
You used to look at me
with some kind of, uh...

1203
01:26:59,023 --> 01:27:01,693
I dunno --

1204
01:27:01,777 --> 01:27:03,237
pride.

1205
01:27:05,949 --> 01:27:07,701
It's gone, though.

1206
01:27:07,784 --> 01:27:10,538
I'm so confused.
Why?

1207
01:27:10,621 --> 01:27:12,707
I think he needs me.

1208
01:27:12,790 --> 01:27:14,209
Is it because you feel

1209
01:27:14,292 --> 01:27:16,628
that... that you owe him
for...

1210
01:27:16,670 --> 01:27:18,130
for Nick?

1211
01:27:19,674 --> 01:27:22,552
No, it's not like that at all.
It's, uh...

1212
01:27:22,636 --> 01:27:24,930
It's more.
Well, I... I don't think

1213
01:27:24,972 --> 01:27:26,474
I could hear it.

1214
01:27:30,145 --> 01:27:33,274
I think we both need a little
time. I need a little time.

1215
01:27:35,819 --> 01:27:38,530
I'm just gonna go
and get the kids.

1216
01:29:08,266 --> 01:29:09,601
Julia!

1217
01:29:10,769 --> 01:29:12,271
Julie!

1218
01:29:39,262 --> 01:29:40,764
I'm here.
You came.

1219
01:29:53,989 --> 01:29:57,493
The turn is two clicks
off the main road,

1220
01:29:57,576 --> 01:29:59,120
and up the hill...

1221
01:29:59,162 --> 01:30:01,414
Is it the only house up there?

1222
01:30:02,958 --> 01:30:06,337
Right, right. And the key
is under the mat. I got that.

1223
01:30:07,505 --> 01:30:09,299
Monica, I don't know
how to thank you.

1224
01:30:11,093 --> 01:30:14,472
What? It's breaking up.
She's gone.

1225
01:30:14,514 --> 01:30:16,600
Careful!

1226
01:30:17,684 --> 01:30:19,478
Hey, I'm an excellent driver.

1227
01:30:19,520 --> 01:30:20,938
Okay?

1228
01:30:21,022 --> 01:30:25,861
I am sorry. Um, for me,
it is all too complicated, this car.

1229
01:30:25,945 --> 01:30:29,366
I don't understand it.
Nick'll explain it to you.

1230
01:30:29,449 --> 01:30:31,869
You should learn how to drive
anyway.

1231
01:30:34,038 --> 01:30:36,332
We will see. We'll see.

1232
01:31:47,920 --> 01:31:50,090
Don't be afraid.

1233
01:31:50,132 --> 01:31:53,469
I'll teach you.
I'll teach you everything.

1234
01:31:57,766 --> 01:31:59,727
The key under the mat.

1235
01:34:46,766 --> 01:34:49,143
It's easy.

1236
01:35:36,160 --> 01:35:39,205
Slowly. Slowly.

1237
01:35:39,247 --> 01:35:40,749
Okay?

1238
01:36:21,424 --> 01:36:22,133
Hi, Rebecca.
 

1239
01:36:23,384 --> 01:36:26,221
Hi, guys. This is Julie.

1240
01:36:26,305 --> 01:36:29,976
Uh, Henry, um, I'm up
at Monica's cabin for a while.

1241
01:36:30,059 --> 01:36:32,729
I'll probably stay here
a couple of days

1242
01:36:32,813 --> 01:36:36,818
and, uh, the phone... Well,
there is no phone in the cabin

1243
01:36:36,901 --> 01:36:39,237
and the cell phone's
not working, so...

1244
01:36:39,321 --> 01:36:41,657
I guess I'll just call you back.

1245
01:36:43,451 --> 01:36:44,619
Okay.

1246
01:36:44,702 --> 01:36:46,162
Bye.

1247
01:36:47,956 --> 01:36:49,625
See this dog?

1248
01:36:49,667 --> 01:36:51,794
My father had one just like her.

1249
01:36:51,836 --> 01:36:53,630
It was his favourite.
 

1250
01:36:53,672 --> 01:36:55,215
 
When I was seven,

1251
01:36:55,299 --> 01:36:57,677
