The veterinarian

1252
01:36:57,760 --> 01:37:01,056
wanted to put him to sleep,
but I knew I could help him.

1253
01:37:01,139 --> 01:37:02,432
How did you know?

1254
01:37:02,516 --> 01:37:03,976
Just felt it.

1255
01:37:04,018 --> 01:37:07,814
This kind of urge
that I had to do it,

1256
01:37:07,856 --> 01:37:09,441
because I had this power.

1257
01:37:09,525 --> 01:37:11,110
As a matter of fact,

1258
01:37:11,193 --> 01:37:13,321
the dog
was my first real patient.

1259
01:37:14,906 --> 01:37:16,867
I took his head in my hands

1260
01:37:16,909 --> 01:37:19,537
and he was healed, in no time.

1261
01:37:19,620 --> 01:37:21,247
After I saved the dog,
my father

1262
01:37:21,331 --> 01:37:22,624
didn't beat me anymore.

1263
01:37:22,707 --> 01:37:26,045
Even though I was still
a lousy pupil at school.

1264
01:37:27,088 --> 01:37:29,090
The dog is still alive.
My father,

1265
01:37:29,174 --> 01:37:30,842
he is dead, but the dog
is still running around.

1266
01:37:30,884 --> 01:37:31,719
How old is he?

1267
01:37:31,802 --> 01:37:34,430
Forty-three years old.

1268
01:37:34,514 --> 01:37:37,267
You liar!

1269
01:37:37,350 --> 01:37:39,269
I can't believe
a word that you say.

1270
01:37:41,397 --> 01:37:44,860
And then, at the asylum,
the same thing happened

1271
01:37:44,901 --> 01:37:47,738
Iike when I was little boy.
The director

1272
01:37:47,780 --> 01:37:51,159
called a specialist
from a parapsychological institute

1273
01:37:51,243 --> 01:37:55,581
and they start to make this test
with me.

1274
01:37:55,665 --> 01:37:57,208
Was it terrible?

1275
01:37:57,250 --> 01:38:01,255
Oh, no, it was not horrible.
Just, I, uh...

1276
01:38:01,338 --> 01:38:02,673
Iosing time.

1277
01:38:02,757 --> 01:38:06,094
Then they see my gifts,
so they started to send me

1278
01:38:06,136 --> 01:38:08,764
to different big shots
Yeah, politicals, yes?

1279
01:38:08,848 --> 01:38:12,686
So I cured them and theirwives
and their mothers-in-law

1280
01:38:12,769 --> 01:38:16,482
and... And one of them arranged
passport for me, so I went abroad

1281
01:38:16,565 --> 01:38:21,196
and I started to healing people
all the time.

1282
01:38:21,280 --> 01:38:24,617
I travelled and healed, travelled
and healed -- all the time.

1283
01:38:24,659 --> 01:38:26,911
That was my life.

1284
01:38:28,330 --> 01:38:30,499
Do you regret?

1285
01:38:30,583 --> 01:38:32,210
What?

1286
01:38:32,293 --> 01:38:34,796
Things you had before.
Before you met me.

1287
01:38:34,880 --> 01:38:37,633
Oh, no.

1288
01:38:37,716 --> 01:38:40,428
I have nothing before you.
Nothing.

1289
01:38:47,145 --> 01:38:48,396
Julie?

1290
01:38:48,480 --> 01:38:49,940
And the children?

1291
01:38:51,901 --> 01:38:55,113
You know Nicholas
is already very fond of you.

1292
01:38:55,155 --> 01:38:58,117
They'll love you.
It's impossible not to love you.

1293
01:39:03,081 --> 01:39:06,001
It's that I am not sure

1294
01:39:06,085 --> 01:39:09,005
if you love me
because Nicholas recovered

1295
01:39:09,088 --> 01:39:11,591
or is it because it's me.

1296
01:39:11,675 --> 01:39:14,053
How can you be so stupid?

1297
01:39:14,136 --> 01:39:15,304
Julie.
Mm.

1298
01:39:15,388 --> 01:39:18,225
What kind of life
you can have with me?

1299
01:39:18,308 --> 01:39:22,313
We'll travel to England.
You can heal all those mad cows.

1300
01:39:22,396 --> 01:39:26,610
We'll make a fortune.
No, I don't want to do it more.

1301
01:39:26,693 --> 01:39:29,697
I want to be with you.

1302
01:39:29,780 --> 01:39:30,448
Always.

1303
01:39:30,531 --> 01:39:33,368
And me with you.

1304
01:39:35,246 --> 01:39:38,374
I'll wrap you up in my big coat.

1305
01:39:38,458 --> 01:39:40,043
